President Obama announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. The nominations include Robert F. Cohen, Jr. for Member of the Federal Mine Safety and Health Review Commission, and Timothy J. Feighery for Chairman of the Foreign Claims Settlement Commission of the United States. The appointments include Audrey Choi as a Member of the Community Development Advisory Board, Nani A. Coloretti as Assistant Secretary for Management at the Department of the Treasury, Tanya M. Fiddler as a Member of the Community Development Advisory Board, and Doug Low as a Member of the Community Development Advisory Board. These individuals bring a depth of experience and dedication to their roles, and President Obama looks forward to working with them in the future.